{"lemma":"عِقابُ","slug":"عِقابُ","root":"ع.ق.ب","root_slug":"ع-ق-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ق-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عِقاب","root":"عقب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":20},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29845","n29846"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%90%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَاقَبَ (ʕāqaba, “to punish”) (form III)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"punishment, infliction of punishment","examples":[{"text":"إِنَّ رَبَّكَ لَذُو مَغْفِرَةٍ وَذُو عِقَابٍ أَلِيمٍ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"eagle"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕi.qaːb/","/ʕu.qaːb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29845","headword_ar":"عُقَابٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eagle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain bird,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of those that prey,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) of the fem. gender: (S, O, Msb:) [though] applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but with this distinction, that you say of the male,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA EuqaAbN *akarN","text_ar":"هٰذَا عُقَابٌ ذَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a male eagle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or it is only"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and a bird of another kind couples with it; whence Ibn-'Oneyn says, satirizing a person named Ibn-Seyyideh, Say thou to Ibn-Seyyideh,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"maA A^anota A_il~aA kaA@loEuqaAbi faA^um~uhu\n                      \n                     \n                        maEoruwfapN walahu A^abN majohuwlu"},{"kind":"text","text":"[“"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art not other than the like of the eagle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"”"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for his mother is known, but he has a father unknown"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (MF, TA:) the pl. (of pauc., S, O) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoqubN","text_ar":"اَعْقُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) because it is of the fem. gender and the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEulN","text_ar":"اَفْعُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"specially belongs to pls. of fem. nouns [though not to such exclusively], (S, O,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoqibapN","text_ar":"اَعْقِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kr, TA,) and (of mult., S, O)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqobaAnN","text_ar":"عِقْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqaAy^ibu","text_ar":"عَقَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to AHei, but Ed-Demámeenee thinks this to be strange; and pl. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqaAbiynu","text_ar":"عَقَابِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqobaAnu Aljiro*aAni","text_ar":"عِقْبَانُ الجِرْذَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The eagles that prey upon the large field-rats"},{"kind":"text","text":"] are not black, but of the colour termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuhobap","text_ar":"كُهْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and no use is made of their feathers, except that boys feather with them round-topped pointless arrows. (AHn, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuqaAbu","text_ar":"العُقَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One of the northern constellations,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Aquila,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the stars of which are nine within the figure, and six without, of the former of which are three well known, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~asoru AlT~aAy^iru","text_ar":"النَّسْرُ الطَّايِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (Kzw.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqaAb","text_ar":"عُقَاب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the banner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"standard;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O;) [app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the flag attached to a lance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is bound"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a lance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for a prefect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"governor;"},{"kind":"text","text":"likened to the bird so called; and of the fem. gender. (L, TA.) It is also the name of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The banner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"standard, of the Prophet."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqaAbN","text_ar":"عُقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A large banner"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"standard."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAyapN","text_ar":"غَايَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": so in the saying of Aboo-Dhu-eyb, describing wine,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"lahaA gaAyapN tahodiY AlkiraAma EuqaAbuhaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It has a banner, which guides the generous;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as the military banner guides and attracts warriors: for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAyapN","text_ar":"غَايَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"sometimes signifies a sign which the vintner used to set up to attract customers]: the repetition is approvable because of the difference of the two words in themselves: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqobaAnN","text_ar":"عِقْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqaAbN","text_ar":"عُقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A black she-camel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as being likened to the bird. [so called], (AA, O.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stone"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of rock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"L)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protruding in the inside of a well, which lacerates the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leathern"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bucket;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sometimes it is before"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the casing"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of stones"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bricks"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is when a mass of stone becomes displaced; and sometimes the water-drawer stands upon it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is of the fem. gender: pl. as above. (TA.) And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stone upon which the waterer stands,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K,) [accord. to SM,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"projecting beyond the casing in a well,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the same that is meant in the next preceding sentence, (TA,) [but this I think doubtful, for Sgh adds,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between two stones which support it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) Accord. to IAar, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabiylap","text_ar":"قَبِيلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a mass of stone, or rock, at the mouth of a well; and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqaAbaAni","text_ar":"عُقَابَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two masses of stone"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the two sides of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qbylp","text_ar":"قبيلة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supporting it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mass of stone, projecting in the side of a mountain, like a stair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"series of steps:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ascent, like stairs, in the side of a mountain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hill;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAbiyapN","text_ar":"رَابِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything elevated, that is not very long"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tall."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K. *) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A channel by which water flows to a trough,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tank."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing resembling an almond, that comes forth in one of the legs of a beast."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A small thread that enters into"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passes through"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two bores of the ring of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quroT","text_ar":"قُرْط"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ear-drop"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (O, K, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2103},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"latter is bound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fastened:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) or, accord. to Az, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thread that binds the two extremities of the ring of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quroT","text_ar":"قُرْط"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b10-  Accord. to Th, it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Garments of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboraAd","text_ar":"اَبْرَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodN","text_ar":"بُرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]. (TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xudaAriy~apN","text_ar":"خُدَارِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b11-  And accord. to Kr, [in the Munjid,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarovN","text_ar":"حَرْثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A ploughshare"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b12-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoqaAbN","text_ar":"اَعْقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b13-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuqaAbaAni","text_ar":"العُقَابَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two pieces of wood between which a man is extended to be flogged:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two pieces of wood which are set up, stuck in the ground, between which he who is beaten,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he who is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crucified, is extended."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","Msb","MF","TA","Kr","L"]},{"entry_id":"n29846","headword_ar":"عِقَابٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqibN","text_ar":"عَقِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last quarter.       -A2-  It is also pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqabapN","text_ar":"عَقَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S, &c.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoqaAbN","text_ar":"اَعْقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}